snippet.textDisplay: VAR should not be used for these marginal offside decisions.  The VAR cameras run at 50 fps (don't ask me why they aren't using a higher frame rate) and this allows for a huge margin of error (as much as 15 cms if only the attacker is moving towards the goal and as much as 30 cms if the last defender is moving in the opposite direction).  Seems to me that someone is getting very rich selling the FA snakeoil ... and ruining football in the process.
